title: Cross-cap surface
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

The //cross-cap surface,// parametrized by

$$
f\colon S^2 \to \R^3,\quad
\begin{pmatrix} x \\ y \\ z \end{pmatrix} \mapsto
  \begin{pmatrix} yz \\ zx \\ \frac 1 2 (x^2-y^2) \end{pmatrix}
$$

satisfies $$f(-p) = f(p)$$ and can therefore be viewed as representing $$\RP^2.$$